        <h1 class="post__title">Frontmatter Edge Cases Test</h1>

        <h1 id="frontmatter-edge-cases-test">Frontmatter Edge Cases Test</h1>
<p>This post tests various edge cases that a custom frontmatter parser needs to handle:</p>
<h2 id="special-characters-in-strings">Special Characters in Strings</h2>
<p>The frontmatter includes:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Quotes in strings</strong>: <code>special_chars: String with &quot;quotes&quot; and &#39;apostrophes&#39;</code></li>
<li><strong>Colons in values</strong>: <code>url_with_colon: https://example.com:8080/path</code></li>
<li><strong>Multi-word array items</strong>: <code>multiword_tag: [web development, static-site generators, unit testing]</code></li>
</ul>
<h2 id="date-parsing">Date Parsing</h2>
<p>The <code>date: 2025-01-15</code> should be parsed as a Date object.</p>
<h2 id="boolean-values">Boolean Values</h2>
<p>The <code>draft: false</code> should be parsed as boolean <code>false</code>, not the string <code>&quot;false&quot;</code>.</p>
<h2 id="why-these-tests-matter">Why These Tests Matter</h2>
<p>A custom frontmatter parser needs to handle:</p>
<ol>
<li>Quoted strings with special characters</li>
<li>Unquoted strings containing colons (like URLs)</li>
<li>Arrays with items containing spaces</li>
<li>Proper type conversion (dates, booleans)</li>
</ol>
<p>If this post renders correctly and appears in the index/feeds, the parser is working!</p>


